The paper discusses the verification of a hybrid agent architecture for an autonomous vehicle platooning system, which involves aspects of robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The system also has real-time (cs.SY) and spatial (cs.SE) aspects that need to be verified. The paper also mentions the use of algorithmic and deductive verification techniques, which are relevant to the field of logic and computation (cs.LO).
